Method Detail

getContactSubtypeFilter

public java.lang.String[] getContactSubtypeFilter()
Get the Contact subtype security filter which will contain an array of contact subtypes which can be viewed by the current user. All subtypes in the array are subtype of the searchContactType or equals to searchContactType When the user has the permission to see all subtypes of searchContactRootType, then the array contains just the searchContactRootType.

Returns:
an array of contact subtypes viewable by the current user. Return null when the subtype filter is not set yet. NOTE: if setContactSubtypeFilter() is not called first, then getContactSubtypeFilter() return null

setContactSubtypeFilter

public void setContactSubtypeFilter(java.lang.String[] subtypeFilter)
Set the Contact subtype security filter which is basically an array of contact subtypes (relatively name) which can be viewed by the current user. All subtypes in the array are subtype of the searchContactType or equals to searchContactType When the user has the permission to see all subtypes of searchContactRootType, then the array contains just the searchContactRootType.

Parameters:
subtypeFilter - - an array of subtype relative names to filter out in the remote query
